abstract: "UIDT v3.9 presents a high-precision, evidence-classified framework for the information-geometric coupling of QFT-sector observables and gravitational parameters. It implements a Four-Pillar Architecture: (1) a mathematically closed derivation of the Yang-Mills Mass Gap (Delta approx 1.710 GeV) verified by constructive fixed-point methods (Category A: internal mathematical consistency, external evaluation pending); (2) cosmological calibration using DESI DR2 + JWST/ACT constraints with explicit evidence tagging (Category C); (3) laboratory-scale falsification targets (Casimir / scalar-sector tests) with conservative status (Category D where unverified); and (4) Photonic Isomorphism, interpreting the UIDT vacuum scalar density S(x) as an effective refractive index channel in nonlocal metamaterials, predicting a critical index n_critical = gamma approx 16.339. The v3.9 manuscript also introduces the torsion binding energy E_T as the missing link between the geometric vacuum scale and the empirically anchored vacuum resonance. Known limitations include a 23% electron mass residual, an unresolved 10^10 holographic scale factor, and a phenomenological gamma parameter pending full RG derivation."
